Package com.example.projectv2.Model

Class Event

java.lang.Object
com.example.projectv2.Model.Event
All Implemented Interfaces:
Serializable
public class Event extends Object implements Serializable
Model class for Events

Represents an event with details such as name, owner, description, rules, dates, and associated facility. The class is Serializable, allowing instances to be easily passed in intents.

      public Event(String eventID, String owner, String name, String detail, String rules, String deadline, String startDate, String ticketPrice, android.net.Uri imageUri, String facility)
      Constructs an Event with specified details.
      Parameters:
      eventID - the unique identifier for the event
      owner - the owner or creator of the event
      name - the name of the event
      detail - a description of the event
      rules - the rules or guidelines for the event
      deadline - the registration deadline for the event
      startDate - the start date of the event
      ticketPrice - the price of the event's ticket
      imageUri - the URI of the event's image, if any
      facility - the facility where the event is hosted
